Optimizer Capabilities:
  - store-recall-peephole: candidate; Elides immediate X->П r / П->X r pairs when no exact-machine effect is crossed.
  - stack-current-x-scheduling: candidate; Keeps a just-computed value in X for a following commutative use and removes the temporary store after data-flow proof.
  - tail-call-lowering: active; Replaces subroutine calls in tail position with direct jumps so rule factoring and terminal branches do not force extra returns or branch hops.
  - return-zero-jump: candidate; Uses В/О as one-cell БП 01 only when the return stack is known empty.
  - vo-return-body-reorder: candidate; Candidate: reorder HEAD/MAIN/SUB so a subroutine return lands at the program head and a ПП/В/О pair collapses. Single-use procedures are already inlined and tail-position calls already become direct jumps, so the remaining gain needs a global layout search with no proven safe trigger on the current programs.
  - super-number-deferred-normalization: candidate; Candidate: keep an un-normalized super-number (extra hidden mantissa digits) to defer a range/error check. The reference emulator models only the 8 visible mantissa digits, so the hidden-digit behavior the idiom relies on cannot be reproduced or safely proven, and no language construct produces it.
  - packed-position-type: candidate; Candidate: a language-level packed position type N.0000H carrying an integer position plus packed (hex) fractional sub-coordinates. The dual-use round-trip (К [x] recovers the position, К {x} recovers the packed fraction) is already exploited by constants-dual-use; a dedicated type would only add language surface that no current program consumes.
  - coord-list-scaled-decimal: candidate; Stores 10x10 board coordinates as y.x decimal values when all visible uses allow it, so row/column/diagonal scans avoid repeated /10 digit extraction.
  - dual-constant-sign-digit: candidate; Candidate: a language intent for a dual constant 1.|-00 plus compact sign-digits (2N..9N) and their comparison semantics. The negative-zero comparison behavior is already active through the negative-zero-threshold family; no current program needs the additional sign-digit literal surface.
  - branch-removal: candidate; Umbrella rule for replacing provably equivalent conditionals with branchless arithmetic, sign, extrema, or masked updates.
  - zero-condition-test: active; Uses direct F x?0 tests when one side of a condition is a proved zero, avoiding a zero literal and subtraction.
  - dispatch-compare-chain: active; Lowers high-level command dispatch automatically; small proven dispatches may use indirect or super-dark dispatch.

Machine Features Used:
  - indirect-flow: Optimizer selected register-held branch addresses for one-cell indirect flow.; К БП/К ПП/К x?0 indirect flow commands are available to the optimizer.
  - error-stops: Compiler emitted a domain-error pause or explicit trap.; Domain-error stops are available only when the source semantics permits trap-like termination.
  - code-data-overlay: Layout marked address cells as reusable code/data overlay candidates.; Address operands, constants, opcodes, and display bytes may share cells after conflict checks.
  - display-bytes: Display lowering marked cells as packed display-byte candidates.; Packed display bytes, hexadecimal mantissa digits, and sign-digit forms are available.
  - address-constants: Layout marked address cells as reusable constants.; Address cells may double as constants for indirect flow and data transforms.

Proofs:
  - return-stack-empty: not-needed; Program uses subroutine calls, so В/О-as-jump is not assumed globally.
  - indirect-addressing-ranges: proved; Indirect selectors are rewritten only after local data-flow proves a stable target, a compiler-owned address preload, or the fractional R0 sentinel shape.
  - value-ranges: proved; Collected source ranges for charges, floor, room, scan.
  - observability: proved; Visible state is limited by display output: floor, row.
  - display-byte-observable-boundary: assumed; Display-byte candidates are bounded by display output and the exact mk61 profile.

Rejected Candidates:
  - direction_dispatch/indirect-register-flow: 17 steps; rejected; selector is key-valued, not address-valued, and building an address register would not beat the compare-chain
  - direction_dispatch/dark-indirect-table: 4 steps; considered; layout proof did not establish a conflict-free address/data table for this site
  - direction_dispatch/super-dark-dispatch: 3 steps; considered; selector is key-valued, and layout proof did not place one-command cases at 48..53 with tails at 01..06
  - if@95/negative-zero-threshold-flow: 9 steps; Negative-zero threshold flow estimated at 9 cells; ordinary condition was shorter (5).

Cell Roles:
  01: 24 address, constant, overlay - address can be reused as constant; code/data overlay allowed
  25: 91 address, constant, overlay - address can be reused as constant; code/data overlay allowed
