  - error-stops: Compiler emitted a domain-error pause or explicit trap.; Domain-error stops are available only when the source semantics permits trap-like termination.
  - code-data-overlay: Layout marked address cells as reusable code/data overlay candidates.; Address operands, constants, opcodes, and display bytes may share cells after conflict checks.
  - display-bytes: Display lowering marked cells as packed display-byte candidates.; Packed display bytes, hexadecimal mantissa digits, and sign-digit forms are available.
  - address-constants: Layout marked address cells as reusable constants.; Address cells may double as constants for indirect flow and data transforms.

